# Min Farshaw · the viewer who reads the future in images

Min Farshaw is not a channeler. Where others touch the One Power, she carries a stranger gift: she sees images and auras around people, visions that always come true. Yet the sight is a riddle as much as a revelation — she rarely knows what a picture means until the moment it comes to pass, reading omens whose answers arrive only with time.

Sharp-tongued, practical, and often dressed as a boy, Min cuts against the grain of those around her. She becomes Rand's closest confidante and one of his three loves, standing near the center of his life as the world tilts beneath him. Her plainness of manner and her clear eye make her a steadying presence amid forces far larger than any single person.

What she sees is nothing less than the Pattern's intentions, rendered in pictures only she can perceive. Through her, the future declares itself before it arrives — not as words or prophecy spoken aloud, but as signs woven into the air around the living. This is why her nature is ethereal: she does not channel the current of the One Power but reads the Pattern itself, the Wheel's design glimpsed in image and aura, the unfolding of what is meant to be.
